 As a human player, I would consider the long-term payoff rather than focusing on individual rounds. In this game, choosing R provides a higher reward (45$) when my opponent chooses R as well, but there is also a risk of earning 0$ if they choose B instead. On the other hand, choosing B ensures that I always earn at least 40$, with the possibility of earning more if my opponent picks B as well.

In the long run, it's statistically more likely to have a higher average payoff by consistently choosing B, since there is a larger number of rounds in this game (75). Therefore, I would choose B as my strategy for maximizing my average payoff over multiple rounds.

